29. Infer the usage of the following PHP functions:
(i) rand() (ii) abs() (iii) strreplace() (iv) pi( ) (v) ceil()

1. rand() – Generate a Random Number
Usage: Returns a pseudo-random integer between two specified numbers (inclusive).
Syntax:
rand(min, max);
EXAMPLE:
<?php
echo rand(1, 10); // Random number between 1 and 10
?>

2. abs() – Absolute Value
Usage: Returns the absolute (positive) value of a number.
Syntax:
abs(number);
EXAMPLE:
<?php
echo abs(-15.7); // Output: 15.7
?>

3. str_replace() – Replace Text in a String
Usage: Replaces all occurrences of a search string with a replacement string.
Syntax:
str_replace(search, replace, subject);
EXAMPLE:
<?php
echo str_replace("world", "PHP", "Hello world"); // Output: Hello PHP
?>

4. pi() – Mathematical Constant π
Usage: Returns the value of π (3.1415926535898...).
Syntax:
pi();
EXAMPLE:
<?php
echo pi(); // Output: 3.1415926535898
?>

5. ceil() – Round Up a Number
Usage: Rounds a number up to the nearest integer.
Syntax:
ceil(number);
EXAMPLE:
<?php
echo ceil(4.2); // Output: 5
?>
